3. Kong Gateway Overview

Kong Gateway is an open-source, cloud-native API Gateway built on NGINX + Lua.

Used for:

Traffic management
Security
API authentication
Rate limiting
Logging
Monitoring
Load balancing
Why Kong is Popular
High performance
Plugin architecture
Kubernetes friendly
Works with Docker
Enterprise support
Easy declarative config
4. Reverse Proxy vs API Gateway
Reverse Proxy

A reverse proxy forwards client requests to backend servers.

Example:

Client → NGINX → Backend

Used for:

SSL termination
Static file serving
Load balancing
API Gateway

API Gateway is an advanced reverse proxy with:

Authentication
Rate limiting
Metrics
Plugins
Request transformation
Developer portal
Kong = Reverse Proxy + Smart Features